^B@2^*BHoward Schutzman: ^*N|cp||at|If right hand opponent bids, then responder is relieved of having to bid. (No ambulance ride if he passes -:). Therefore, any suit bid by responder should show some values, and should be treated as ^*Bforcing^*N by the takeout doubler. The only exception is redouble -- in that case, the opponents have the majority of the points, so if responder has a clear preference for one suit, it should be bid, and the takeout doubler should not consider this bid forcing (in fact, takeout doubler should virtually always pass).|
PG| ***** 54 ***** |


AT|

^B@2^*BMM: ^*NI see that Barbara likes to join the discussion.|
