^B@2^*BBarbara Seagram: ^*N|cp||at|With pleasure. Until now, we have assumed that opener’s partner passed over partner’s double. If he makes a bid, things change dramatically as you can now pass whenever you have a poor hand. You should have 8+ points (including distribution) to respond if you are not forced to do so. This is called making a "free bid." We know that MM likes illustrate every example at a table. So let us look at a few.|
